page.title: 10WOODLAND (continued)
page.content: Sulham Wood was originally beech woodland.It has now fine examples of oak,beech,poplar,Norway Maple,Douglas fir,Red cedar,Western hemlock,among many others.Some of the flowers we have seen in our walks include primroses,dog violets and ecstensive areas of blue_bells and buttercups. Traces of rabbits,badgers and foxes have been seen.Squirrels are there in large numbers and occasionally deer step daintily between the trees. There are a number of families of Jays,Magpies and Green Woodpeckers there and we believe that we have seen a Yellow_Hammer flying near the road.Owls and Pheasants are abundant and Tits and Finches can often be seen.
